<body>
    <header>
        <h1>AIRDeM 2025</h1>
        <p>First International Workshop on AI for Research Data Management</p>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>About AIRDeM</h2>
        <p>
            In today's data-driven research landscape, effective Research Data Management (RDM) practices are crucial for unlocking the full potential of innovative discoveries, while upholding the integrity and reproducibility of scientific work. 
            The Artificial Intelligence for Research Data Management (AIRDeM) workshop explores the application of AI-driven solutions and interdisciplinary approaches for RDM, focusing on topics like automated metadata extraction, annotation, and generation. 
        </p>
        <p>
            AIRDeM aims to gather research papers and practical implementations (demos) across multiple domains, including life sciences, earth sciences, and digital humanities. This workshop fosters interdisciplinary collaboration to address RDM challenges and advance FAIR (Findability, Accessibility, Interoperability, Reusability) practices through cutting-edge AI applications.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Call for Contributions</h2>
        <p>
            We invite submissions in the following categories:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Research Papers:</strong> Innovative research on AI-driven solutions to RDM challenges or FAIR data practices.</li>
            <li><strong>Demos:</strong> Real-world AI tools designed to improve RDM and FAIRification processes.</li>
            <li><strong>Posters:</strong> Visual presentations highlighting insights, approaches, or tools for tackling RDM challenges.</li>
            <li><strong>"Bring Your Challenge":</strong> Abstracts outlining RDM challenges to solve collaboratively during the workshop.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Program Overview</h2>
        <p>The workshop includes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Keynote Talk</li>
            <li>Paper Presentations</li>
            <li>Interactive "Bring Your Challenge" Session</li>
            <li>Panel Discussion</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Workshop Details</h2>
        <p>
            AIRDeM will be held as part of the Extended Semantic Web Conference (ESWC). 
            Stay tuned for updates on the exact date, location, and submission deadlines.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/HajiraJabeen/BIK-AI4RDM/" target="_blank">Visit our GitHub Repository</a> for more information.
        </p>
    </section>

